From: J.D. Oder II
Sent: Sunday, August 18, 2019 3:43 PM
To: 'rkennedy@firstdata.com'
Subject: Fun Sunday

Hey Rob,

Hope you are having a great weekend.

I'm sure the last thing you want to do is work but I had a couple
things I wanted to share with you.

One very fun topic is that the Golden Nugget is moving forward with
Shift4 and are signing our contract tomorrow, they are very excited!

On the other hand, I have a very big concern. When you and I first met
to discuss partnering it was because CardConnect had some major gaps
in their product offering, especially as it relates to the enterprise
gaming and hospitality space. In order for this partnership to be
successful we need to be working together.

As it stands right now, we have several major competitive
disadvantages. We spoke recently about the Oracle upgrade fees, which
is obviously a huge issue. The fact that CardConnect doesn't offer
tokenization with i4Go is also a show stopper.

Furthermore, the lack of support for EMV devices with some of the
largest gaming systems is a major problem.

Over the past few months while working with your team, I've come to
realize that there may be serious underlying issues that need to be
addressed.

The fact that CardConnect, doesn't support group codes or advanced
deposits doesn't bode well for the future. I keep getting told
different stories about what the future holds.

We are excited about the pipeline we have been building, but it is
very vulnerable. We need to discuss these issues promptly.

In good faith, we have referred a large existing merchant that we
have a great relationship with to you for US processing business,
Yankee Stadium.

I was also planning on having your team take over Mohegan Sun as well
as Resorts World.

CardConnect has many features that don't seem to be available to
Shift4, but should be such as American Express opt blue.

Finally, the fact that CardConnect's board pricing is lower for us,
really doesn't make sense. As a partner we should be getting better
pricing than a customer especially when the product offering we are
given is inferior.

Shift4 has some of the largest and best integrated partners. We have
seen great strategic advantage by working closely with them in the
past, but this is not a one-way street.

J.D.

From: J.D. Oder II
Sent: Sunday, August 18, 2019 3:43 PM
To: rkennedy@firstdata.com
Subject: Fun Sunday

Hey Rob,

Hope you are having a great weekend.

I'm sure the last thing you want to do is work but I had a couple things I wanted to share with you.

One very fun topic is that the Golden Nugget is moving forward with Shift4 and are signing our
contract tomorrow, they are very excited!

On the other hand, I have a very big concern. When you and I first met to discuss partnering it was
because CardConnect had some major gaps in their product offering, especially as it relates to the
enterprise gaming and hospitality space. In order for this partnership to be successful we need to be
working together.

As it stands right now, we have several major competitive disadvantages. We spoke recently about
the Oracle upgrade fees, which is obviously a huge issue. The fact that CardConnect doesn't offer
tokenization with i4Go is also a show stopper. Furthermore, the lack of support for EMV devices with
some of the largest gaming systems is a major problem.

Over the past few months while working with your team, I've come to realize that there may be serious
underlying issues that need to be addressed.
The fact that CardConnect, doesn't support group codes or advanced deposits doesn't bode well for
the future. I keep getting told different stories about what the future holds.

We are excited about the pipeline we have been building, but it is very vulnerable. We need to discuss
these issues promptly.

In good faith, we have referred a large existing merchant that we have a great relationship with to you
for US processing business, Yankee Stadium.

I was also planning on having your team take over Mohegan Sun as well as Resorts World.
CardConnect has many features that don't seem to be available to Shift4, but should be such as
American Express opt blue.
Finally, the fact that CardConnect's board pricing is lower for us, really doesn't make sense. As a
partner we should be getting better pricing than a customer especially when the product offering we
are given is inferior.
Shift4 has some of the largest and best integrated partners. We have seen great strategic advantage by
working closely with them in the past, but this is not a one-way street.

J.D.
J.D. "Jared" Oder II
Shift4 Payments
